'''Susuki Mizu Shrine''' (й Ҳй ҲеІҗж°ҙзҘһзӨҫ) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in [[:en:Chikuma, Nagano|Chikuma, Nagano]], [[:en:Nagano Prefecture|Nagano Prefecture]], Japan. It is associated with the ancient {{ill|Shrines listed in Engishiki|ja|ејҸеӨ–зӨҫ|1=Shikigeisha|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shrines listed in Engishiki|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikigeisha|qq=}} Susuki Mizu Shrine and held the status of a village shrine (ж—§йғ·зӨҫ) under the [[:en:Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|Modern system of Ranked Shinto shrines]].

== Overview ==
According to shrine tradition, Susuki Mizu Shrine was founded in the second year of the {{ill|HakuhЕҚ period|ja|зҷҪйіі|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/HakuhЕҚ period|qq=}} (673). Initially, it was known as the "HЕҚri Shrine" (зҘқзҘһзӨҫ), a name derived from the [[:en:Engishiki|Engishiki]]. During the [[:en:Zhenguan|JЕҚgan (era)]] era, following flooding of the {{ill|Chikuma River|ja|еҚғжӣІе·қ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chikuma River|qq=}}, the regional governor of [[:en:Hanishina District, Nagano|Hanishina District]], {{ill|Kanasashi no Masanaga|ja|йҮ‘еҲәжӯЈй•·|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanasashi no Masanaga|qq=}}, brought the {{ill|SannЕҚ Gongen|ja|еұұзҺӢжЁ©зҸҫ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/SannЕҚ Gongen|qq=}} from [[:en:Hiyoshi Taisha|Hiyoshi Taisha]] and enshrined it alongside the main deity.

In the Edo period, the shrine received the patronage of the [[:en:Sanada clan|Sanada clan]], who donated 300 koku of land and additional resources for rituals. The shrine was reconstructed by {{ill|Tatekawa WashirЕҚ Tomimasa|ja|з«Ӣе·қе’ҢеӣӣйғҺеҜҢжҳҢ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tatekawa WashirЕҚ Tomimasa|qq=}} in the fourth year of [[:en:Kaei|Kaei]] (1851) following repeated flood damage. In the first year of [[:en:Tenmei|Tenmei]] (1781), the shrine was renamed "Susuki Mizu Shrine" by the head of Shinto priests, the {{ill|Urabe clan|ja|еҚңйғЁж°Ҹ|en|draft:Yoshida family|simple|User:Immanuelle/Urabe_clan|fr|User:Immanuelle/Urabe_clan|lt=Yoshida clan|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Urabe clan|qq=}}.

Previously, the shrine participated in rituals involving the transfer of portable shrines (зҘһијҝ) with {{ill|Amamiya Shrine|ja|йӣЁе®®гҒ®еқҗж—ҘеҗүзҘһзӨҫ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amamiya Shrine|qq=}}, but these were discontinued in the fifth year of [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] (1872).

The shrine site measures approximately 27 ken east-to-west and 34 ken north-to-south. It has been worshipped as a [[:en:Suijin|water god]], serving as the guardian of the Yashiro irrigation system.

== Deities ==

=== Main Enshrined Deities ===
* {{ill|ЕҢkuninushi|ja|еӨ§еӣҪдё»е‘Ҫ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/ЕҢkuninushi|qq=}} (Main deity)
* {{ill|Ikutama-no-Mikoto|ja|еӨ©жҙ»зҺүе‘Ҫ|1=Ame-no-Ikutama|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ikutama-no-Mikoto|13=User:Immanuelle/Ame-no-Ikutama|qq=}} (Ikutama-no-Mikoto)
